screens.screen_desc: The screenshot shows a mobile app interface for entering a delivery address. At the top, there is a map with a pin that can be adjusted. Below the map, the address "17 Washington Street, Hilton SA 5033, Australia" is displayed. There are fields for "Apartment/Suite" and "Entry code." The "Drop-off Options" section allows the user to choose between "Hand it to me" and "Leave it at my door," with the latter option selected. There is a text box for additional instructions, such as ringing the bell after dropoff or leaving the package next to the porch. At the bottom, there is a red "Save Address" button.

ui_elements.text: e.g. ring the bell after dropoff leave next to the porch call upon arrival etc.Do not add order changes or requests here.

flow_desc: The user requests to save an address through a mobile app interface. The process begins with the user entering an address in the "Search for an address" input field. After inputting the address, the user views the search results and taps the location icon for the desired address. The app then displays a map with the selected address, allowing the user to fill in optional details, such as Apartment/Suite and Entry code. Finally, the user selects drop-off options and taps the "Save Address" button, thereby completing the address-saving process effectively.
